title: PT: Paul Feyerabend

; 1924-1994: Paul Feyerabend

* We cannot just confront a theory with "the observed facts"; the identity and the significance of these facts are underdetermined.
* The history of science includes revolutions; "incommensurable" alternatives replace existing theories.
* Science flourishes best when there is a proliferation of different paradigms ("epistemological anarchism").